"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Depriving another person or animal of life, usually by physical force. Scripture identifies various types of killing. While forbidding murder, killing of human beings is permitted in the form of execution and war. Animals may be killed for food or sacrifice, provided that the blood is ritually disposed of.</p>\n<h2>Murder</h2>\n<h3>Murder prohibited by the sixth commandment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:13\">EXO 20:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:17\">DEU 5:17</a></p>\n<h3>Murder prohibited from the time of Noah</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:5-Gen9:6\">GEN 9:5–9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:11\">LEV 17:11</a></p>\n<h3>The life of the murderer is forfeit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:6\">GEN 9:6</a></p>\n<h2>Judicial killing</h2>\n<h3>Judicial killing permitted for capital crimes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:12\">EXO 21:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:18-Exod22:20\">EXO 22:18–22:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:8-Deut17:13\">DEU 17:8–17:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:18-Deut21:21\">DEU 21:18–21:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:21-Deut22:27\">DEU 22:21–22:27</a></p>\n<h3>Executed criminals are under the curse of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:23\">DEU 21:23</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Unintentional killing (manslaughter)</h2>\n<h3>The accidental killing of a fellow human being</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:13\">EXO 21:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:41-Deut4:42\">DEU 4:41–4:42</a></p>\n<h3>The provision of cities of refuge to avoid blood revenge</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:2-Deut19:13\">DEU 19:2–19:13</a> <em>Blood revenge, based on <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:6\">Ge 9:6</a>, refers to the judicial revenge of a family or clan against a man who accidentally kills one of their members.</em></p>\n<h2>Killing in war</h2>\n<h3>Killing in a holy war</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:17\">JOS 6:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:21\">JOS 6:21</a></p>\n<h3>Killing in other wars</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:10-Deut20:15\">DEU 20:10–20:15</a></p>\n<h2>The killing of animals</h2>\n<h3>Regulations for disposal of blood</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:3-Lev17:7\">LEV 17:3–17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:11\">LEV 17:11</a></p>\n<h3>Animals may be killed at a distance from the sanctuary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:15-Deut12:16\">DEU 12:15–12:16</a></p>\n<h3>Limitations on the killing of animals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:6-Deut22:7\">DEU 22:6–22:7</a> <em>This limitation appears to be an attempt to preserve the balance of nature.</em></p>",
